## 10 â€” Glossaryï¼ˆLexiconï¼‰

- **Core Node Shelter OS (CNS-OS)**  
  Operating system for siting and routing short-range core assets inside urban dead-angles and subterranean grids.

- **Core Node (CN)**  
  High-value, range-limited node whose primary requirement is survivable, protected hosting close to what it serves.

- **Urban Dead-Angle Shelter Zone (UDSZ)**  
  Urban region where lines-of-sight and attack paths are structurally constrained and entropically complex.

- **Subterranean Grid Host (SGH)**  
  Underground structure or network suitable for hosting CN functions with strong passive protection.

- **Shelter Routing Envelope (SRE)**  
  Set of access paths designed to keep flows to/from CNs inside protection fields.

- **Î”t_node_access**  
  Additional time external actors require to meaningfully discover or interfere with CNs.

